org.jsonschema2pojo

Class SchemaMapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jsonschema2pojo.SchemaMapper

  • public class SchemaMapper
extends Object
    Generates Java types from a JSON schema. Can accept a factory which will be used to create type generation rules for this mapper.

        Create a schema mapper with the given RuleFactory.
        Parameters:
        ruleFactory - A factory used by this mapper to create Java type generation rules.
        schemaGenerator - the generator that this mapper will use if the config dictates that the input documents are plain json (not json schema)

                               String className,

                               URL schemaUrl)
                                 throws IOException
        Reads a schema and adds generated types to the given code model.
        Parameters:
        codeModel - the java code-generation context that should be used to generated new types
        className - the name of the parent class the represented by this schema
        packageName - the target package that should be used for generated types
        schemaUrl - location of the schema to be used as input
        Returns:
        The top-most type generated from the given file
        Throws:
        IOException - if the schema content cannot be read
